Similar to in issue #208, I have a complicated causal graph containing many nodes but relatively simple data. I am trying to estimate the causal effect of several treatment variables on one outcome (one at a time). 

In dowhy version 0.4, I could identify and estimate each causal effect in a matter of seconds. However, in version 0.5, 0.5.1, 0.6, it takes hours to identify the causal estimates. In issue #208, the problem was an inefficient exhaustive search algorithm which was optimised in version 0.5.1. Is it possible that this could be optimised further or a setting could be added to resort to the non-exhaustive option?

